{
  "stem": "14060.7",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "These are just the personal miniature events which took place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And within a few days, the transport of 6,000 people was broken up into two halves, be-- Buchenwald being a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And half of it was sent-- 3,000 people, or 2,800, 2,900, or something like that-- to Magdeburg, which was a very, very bad camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And those were the people with surnames from A to K.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because in spite of the fact that everybody had a number, they had a record what their name was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And strange enough, that was the method how they split the transport-- not according to height or age or anything, just by the surname, A to K, Magdeburg, K to W, to [?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Trieste. ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Trieste ?] [INAUDIBLE], which later on became known by the name of Ramsdorf.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I will explain to you later how that happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And these were literally work camps, the typical camps where people got not too much food, a lot of long hours and hard work, and under quite inhumane conditions, where literally within months, people were finished.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Now luckily also, my father, my brother and myself were amongst approximately 100 people who were over the quota.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That means we were not sent to Magdeburg-- because our initial was W.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we got left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Now that, I would consider, was the least troublesome period of my camp life, being from 18th of July, I think, when we arrived in Buchenwald, till September.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Now, a lot of things happened in that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I had the advantage of speaking fluent German, that anything which went on was going on in German.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Everybody had to-- even they mumble two words, the language was not any other language.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And you were addressed in German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You had to answer in German.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
